# Twitter Sentiment Analysis Dataset

## Dataset Overview
This dataset contains a collection of tweets used for sentiment analysis. The sentiment of each tweet is labeled as positive, negative, or neutral. The dataset is sourced from the [Sentiment140](http://help.sentiment140.com/for-students/) dataset.

## Download the Dataset
The dataset is too large to be stored directly in this repository. You can download the dataset from the following link:

- [Download Sentiment140 Dataset](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/kazanova/sentiment140)

## Data Preprocessing
To preprocess the dataset, use the code provided in the corresponding Jupyter notebook. This script will clean the data, remove irrelevant information, and prepare it for sentiment analysis.

### Steps to Preprocess the Data

1. **Clone the Repository**:
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/tiwarygaurav/Twitter-Sentiment-Analysis.git
   cd Twitter-Sentiment-Analysis


### Preprocessing Steps in the Notebook

2. **Follow the Steps**:
   Follow the steps outlined in the notebook to preprocess the data.

## Dataset Structure
The dataset contains the following columns:

- `polarity`: The sentiment of the tweet (0 = negative, 2 = neutral, 4 = positive).
- `id`: The unique identifier for each tweet.
- `date`: The date the tweet was posted.
- `query`: The query used to find the tweet (if applicable).
- `user`: The username of the person who posted the tweet.
- `text`: The text of the tweet.

## Additional Information
For more detailed instructions and code, please refer to the [Jupyter Notebooks](notebooks/) and [scripts](scripts/) provided in this repository.

